in mlb for a relief pitcher does sv mean saves how is a save determined does the relief pitcher have to bring his team back from a deficit or does he simply have to hold on and win the game does the starting pitcher then get the w please explain these stats the thing to remember is that the save situation is entirely dependent upon the status of the game when the relief pitcher first takes the mound mlb rule saves for relief pitchers a save is a statistic credited to a relief pitcher as set forth in this rule the official scorer shall credit a pitcher with a save when such pitcher meets all four of the following conditions a he is the finishing pitcher in a game won by his team b he is not the winning pitcher c he is credited with at least a third of an inning pitched and d he satisfies one of the following conditions he enters the game with a lead of no more than three runs and pitches for at least one inning he enters the game regardless of the count with the potential tying run either on base or at bat or on deck that is the potential tying run is either already on base or is one of the first two batters he faces or he pitches for at least three innings Baseball Save (sport) Baseball statistics 1957 World Series Pitcher 2005 World Series 2004 American League Championship Series 1919 World Series Softball International League Pedro Mart__nez Toronto Blue Jays Roger Clemens Boston Red Sox Detroit Tigers St. Louis Cardinals 1987 World Series Closer (baseball) 2004 World Series Earned run average Firpo Marberry Baseball Stars Tris Speaker Nolan Ryan Chicago Cubs October 4 in baseball October 20 in baseball No-hitter Hank Aaron 1987 National League Championship Series Los Angeles Angels of Anaheim Satchel Paige Eric Gagne Batting average Sandy Koufax Houston Astros Andr__s Galarraga Stolen base 2001 World Series Bob Friend Chicago White Sox 1993 World Series October 16 in baseball 1986 World Series Atlanta Braves October 3 in baseball Barry Bonds Laws of cricket Don D